Local authorities on Monday reported that sixteen people were trapped in a coal mine gas explosion in north China’s Shanxi Province. A preliminary investigation showed that 34 miners were working underground at the coal mine in Pingyao County when the blast happened at 1:50 p.m. on Monday. READ ALSO: Man remanded for killing own mother in Ebonyi According to the Shanxi Administration of Coal Mine Safety, so far, 18 people were saved and five others were sent to the hospital. Authorities said rescue work and further investigation are underway. (Xinhua/NAN)